Regarding the grant of revised administrative approval to the budget of the Washim Tap Water Supply Scheme.
Government of Maharashtra
Water Supply and Sanitation Department

Lokmanya Tilak Marg, Mantralaya, Mumbai - Yoo 0019
Date: January 17, 2025
Read: -
1) Administrative approval of Group Gram Panchayat Delhi T.G. Washim Order No.

Grapapuvu / jakr. / pram / 11/2024 d. 15.8.2021 2) Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Washim Original Technical Approval Order No. 13.08.2021 3) Revised Technical Approval Order of the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Washim No. 16.7.2024 4) Letter from CEO, Zilla Parishad, Washim No. Jakr / Grappapuvi / Tansha / 1038/2024, d. 19.7.2024 Preface: -

Washim district. Nimbalwadi Ta. The original budget of Washim Tap Water Supply Scheme was prepared by CEO, Zilla Parishad, Washim vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2. Also, Reference No. Under Section 1, a nominal price of Rs 13,79,644 is granted administrative approval. Also, the Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Washim proposed to give revised administrative approval to the Nal Pani Purbatha Scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here. The letter dated 19.7.2024 has been submitted to the government. Reference 3. Under the letter dated 16.7.2024, the government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price as per the revised technical approval given by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Washim.
The government's decision:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Md. Nimbalwadi Ta. The scheme of Washim Tap Water Supply Scheme is being implemented with an outlay of Rs. 1 crore, subject to the following conditions, on account of increase in the cost of the scheme due to increase in Goods and Services Tax (GST) rates. The revised price of 14,03,431 - (Rupees Fourteen Lakh Three Thousand Four Hundred and Thirty One Only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Supra 2024 / Q. 193 / UT 93 (Office 40.-922744)
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme as well as the terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred every year for implementation, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), reduction in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) According to a CAG report in 2013, 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity of bills due to lack of these maintenance repairs. In fact, in order to make the scheme financially viable, the Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned will be responsible for the necessary increase in the water table rate.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
9) Since no administrative expenditure is admissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if 4% of the administrative expenditure has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.

2. Schemes for which tenders have been floated. The additional cost of the revised cost of the scheme, which has already been approved, should be met from the sanctioned grant of the Jal Jeevan Mission programme only.
